        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 11:44PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1143 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms extending from 7 miles northwest of Henderson to near
Warrenton to near Gasburg. Movement was northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke Rapids, Henderson, Warrenton, Halifax, Norlina, Littleton,
Weldon, Middleburg, Macon, and Medoc Mountain State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
